this whole hospital.

31:02.695 --> 31:04.981
Maybe I'll wipe out
this city like an atomic bomb.

31:05.072 --> 31:07.108
Just leave me alone!
We can't do that.

31:07.199 --> 31:09.190
KAREN: Stop, Ted, stop.

31:13.873 --> 31:15.488
Karen wants you to stop.

31:15.583 --> 31:17.164
How could you say that?

31:17.251 --> 31:21.415
She says you need to listen,
Ted. You never listen.
You're too damn stubborn,

31:21.505 --> 31:23.666
but you're still
her Teddy Bear.

31:23.758 --> 31:26.044
Wait a minute,
you can hear her?

31:26.135 --> 31:28.922
He's telling the truth, Ted.
Listen to him.

31:29.013 --> 31:30.423
(NURSE GROANING)

31:39.231 --> 31:40.767
What's she saying?

31:43.194 --> 31:45.480
She's saying she...

31:46.906 --> 31:48.988
She doesn't blame you

31:49.075 --> 31:52.488
for all the pain
and the worry.

31:53.662 --> 31:56.449
She's saying
it's not your fault, Ted.

31:57.208 --> 31:59.119
She shouldn't be here.

31:59.376 --> 32:00.877
It's not fair.

32:01.128 --> 32:03.244
MATT: She's saying
it never is.

32:03.339 --> 32:05.079
She said
that was the best date.

32:05.174 --> 32:08.917
The picnic on the beach
and it poured sheets
and sheets of rain.

32:09.011 --> 32:11.172
We sat in my car

32:12.515 --> 32:15.473
and listened to the whole
American Beauty album.

32:15.559 --> 32:17.265
She remembers it all.

32:18.938 --> 32:20.894
She always will.

32:22.191 --> 32:23.852
(SOBBING)

32:28.114 --> 32:29.854
What's she saying now?

32:50.970 --> 32:54.554
Hi, this is Niki Sanders
from Las Vegas.

32:55.766 --> 32:57.722
I need your help.

32:57.810 --> 33:01.268
/ know that I’m probably
the last person
that you want to talk to.

33:01.355 --> 33:03.471
You should not
have called me here.

33:03.566 --> 33:05.852
/ know that
l have no right to,

33:06.277 --> 33:08.313
but I need your help.

33:10.239 --> 33:12.571
My husband took my son.

33:13.701 --> 33:15.783
l have nowhere else to go.

33:15.870 --> 33:17.701
I'm sorry. I can't help you.

33:17.872 --> 33:19.533
You have the wrong number.

33:19.623 --> 33:22.581
Hi, hon. Where are the boys?

33:23.836 --> 33:25.417
In the playroom.

33:27.756 --> 33:29.292
Do you still love me, Nathan?

33:29.383 --> 33:30.748
Of course I do.

33:31.594 --> 33:35.007
I know what this chair
means to us as a couple.

33:36.265 --> 33:39.598
But I need you to know
that I'm going to walk again.

33:39.852 --> 33:42.389
The doctors say
it's a long shot,

33:42.855 --> 33:45.392
but I can do it
if I have a reason.

33:47.067 --> 33:49.023
We just need
some hope, Nathan,

33:49.111 --> 33:51.272
that our life
can be like it was.

33:55.868 --> 33:57.449
What Peter said,

33:58.120 --> 34:01.453
about you checking out
a clinic for him
with a doctor,

34:02.917 --> 34:05.124
tell me that's what happened.

34:05.794 --> 34:09.662
If you say it is,
I'll believe you.

34:11.759 --> 34:13.590
Just give me some hope.

34:14.553 --> 34:15.838
It's true.

34:19.850 --> 34:21.351
Come on.

34:24.605 --> 34:26.561
I'm gonna get
the kids ready for bed.

34:26.649 --> 34:27.934
Okay.

34:39.995 --> 34:42.077
What the hell happened?

34:44.166 --> 34:45.747
You should just go.

34:45.834 --> 34:48.541
Niki, what's going on here?
Are you okay?

34:49.296 --> 34:51.287
I said that you can go now.

34:51.924 --> 34:53.505
It's me.

34:53.926 --> 34:56.417
I'm just trying to help
you out, girl, okay?

34:56.512 --> 34:59.094
She doesn't need
your help anymore.

34:59.181 --> 35:00.546
Understand?

35:08.399 --> 35:09.855
Hey.
Hey.

35:09.942 --> 35:11.773
So, they're
gonna run Sprague
through decontamination,

35:11.860 --> 35:14.772
then put him in a special
holding tank downtown.

35:15.030 --> 35:17.282
How'd he cause
all that damage
with his bare hands?

35:17.366 --> 35:19.948
How do you hear
what people are thinking?

35:21.829 --> 35:23.694
You did a greatjob in there.

35:24.456 --> 35:25.662
Well, look,
the guy was losing his wife.

35:25.749 --> 35:28.365
He just wanted
to talk to her, say goodbye.

35:28.460 --> 35:30.291
You talk to
your own wife yet?

35:30.379 --> 35:32.870
You've been
dodging her call all day.

35:36.468 --> 35:39.301
Well, I'm gonna head downtown,
cover Sprague's processing.

35:39.388 --> 35:40.548
Right.

35:44.852 --> 35:46.012
(CELL PHONE DIAL/NG)

35:51.984 --> 35:55.476
Hey, it's me. I actually
thought you might be
home by now.

35:55.863 --> 35:59.151
I'm calling just to talk.

36:02.995 --> 36:06.954
Look, I had this stupid
idea in my head
that I’m losing you.

36:07.708 --> 36:09.118
And I...

36:09.960 --> 36:11.336
| just...

36:11.420 --> 36:16.164
I can't help but have the
feeling that there's something
you're not telling me.

36:16.258 --> 36:21.252
And / don’t
want us to live
with any regret or blame.

36:22.389 --> 36:26.223
I don't know.
I guess I'm just afraid
of things going unsaid.

36:29.146 --> 36:30.386
I love you,

36:33.817 --> 36:37.355
and ljust wanted
to tell you that. You don't
have to call me back.

36:37.446 --> 36:39.562
I'll see you later tonight.

36:46.038 --> 36:47.653
Yes, Mr. Linderman.

36:48.707 --> 36:50.243
It seems my brother
has developed

36:50.334 --> 36:53.292
some sort of emotional
attachment to this painting.

36:54.463 --> 36:59.457
I don't know what will happen
to him if he doesn't get it,
but I'd rather not find out.

36:59.551 --> 37:01.667
Directly to the gallery.

37:02.388 --> 37:06.631
Mr. Linderman,
I appreciate it. Good night.

37:11.939 --> 37:14.146
(DOORBELL BUZZING)

37:18.362 --> 37:20.978
You need to tell
Heidi the truth.

37:21.657 --> 37:26.242
No.
She doesn't need the truth.
She needs hope.

37:26.328 --> 37:27.568
What's that,
some kind of excuse?

37:27.663 --> 37:29.403
I'm not saying
what I did was right.

37:29.498 --> 37:33.036
That girl in Vegas,
I just needed
to be with someone who

37:33.794 --> 37:37.082
didn't make me feel guilty
every time I looked at her.

37:39.299 --> 37:41.255
Did you talk to Linderman?

37:41.343 --> 37:42.753
Yeah. Sit down.

37:42.845 --> 37:44.176
And?

37:47.808 --> 37:49.764
He's not gonna let it go.

37:50.894 --> 37:53.977
Hey, come on,
Pete, just let it go.
It's just a painting.

37:54.064 --> 37:57.022
It's more than that, Nathan.
This is about what's
going on with us.

37:57.109 --> 38:00.818
All right?
This painting is the key.

38:01.780 --> 38:03.941
All right, with this thing,
we could make a difference.

38:04.032 --> 38:06.774
I'm trying to make
a difference, Peter,
the best way I know how.

38:06.869 --> 38:08.484
Flying around, how's that
going to help anybody?

38:08.579 --> 38:11.286
What is that...
I can't... What am I
gonna do when | get there?

38:11.373 --> 38:14.831
I don't have a gun.
I don't have a badge.
I don't know karate.

38:14.918 --> 38:19.378
I guess I could put on
a costume and fly around
and pull cats out of trees.

38:19.590 --> 38:22.081
How's that gonna
make a difference?

38:22.217 --> 38:24.879
You're not gonna
know until you try.

38:25.679 --> 38:28.295
